  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot of plenty of<strong> boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 10-15 min or until they're fork-tender</p><p>Once cooked, drain and set aside to steam dry in the pot</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/skin-on-waxy-potatoes-1601641613239-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/skin-on-waxy-potatoes-1601641613239-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/skin-on-waxy-potatoes-1601641613239-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/skin-on-waxy-potatoes-1601641613239-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/skin-on-waxy-potatoes-1601641613239-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add <strong>half</strong> of<strong> </strong>your <strong>white wine vinegar </strong>to a large bowl (you'll use the rest later!) with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and stir until dissolved</p><p>Add your <strong>shredded red cabbage</strong> to the bowl, give everything a good mix up and set aside until later to pickle slightly – this is your <strong>quick-pickled cabbage</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel your <strong>brown onion[s] </strong>and cut in half</p><p>Grate <strong>half </strong>your <strong>onion[s]</strong> and slice the <strong>remaining onion </strong>finely</p><p>Add your<strong> grated onion</strong>, <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong>,<strong> baharat</strong>, <strong>lamb mince</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to a large bowl – this is your<strong> lamb mix</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Knead the <strong>lamb mix </strong>thoroughly with clean hands for 2-3 min (this helps the mixture hold together when cooking) then shape into 3 <strong>koftas </strong>per person</p><p>Tip: Oil your hands slightly to stop the mixture sticking when shaping!</p><p>Add the <strong>koftas</strong> to an <strong>oiled baking tray </strong>(or two!) and put the tray[s] in the oven for 15 min or until  cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>Turkish-style lamb koftas</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium-low heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>natural yoghurt</strong>,<strong> tahini paste </strong>and the <strong>remaining white wine vinegar </strong>to a bowl</p><p>Add a splash of <strong>cold water </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>tahini yoghurt</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add your <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>tomato paste </strong>cook for 1 min</p><p>Add the <strong>drained potatoes</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then crush the <strong>potatoes</strong> lightly and cook for 5-6 min or until they're starting to crisp</p><p>Once the potatoes are crisp, remove the pan from the heat and add the <strong>chopped parsley</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1169.-step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Turkish-style</strong> <strong>lamb koftas</strong> over the<strong> tahini yoghurt </strong>with the <strong>crushed potatoes</strong> and<strong> quick-pickled cabbage</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
